quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  2,44,"What ! you enjoin people to be virtuous and forget it yourselves while you read the book, then have you no sense"
  2,45,And seek help through patience and worship (salat) and this is certainly difficult except for the humble ones
  2,46,those who expect that they will meet their Fosterer and that to Him they will return
  2,47,O children of Israel ! remember My favour with which I favoured you and that I preferably favoured you (compared to others in the) worlds
  2,48,"And guard yourselves against a day when no requital* will be accepted from one person for another in anything nor will recommendation be accepted for him nor will compensation be taken from him nor will they be helped. * Repayment for good or evil, reward or punishment"
  2,49,"And (remember) when We delivered you from the people of Firawn who subjected you to severe punishment, they slew your sons and left your women alive and in that there was a great trial from your Fosterer"
  2,50,and when We parted the sea for you and delivered you and drowned the people of Firawn while you were seeing
  2,51,And when We appointed for Musa forty nights then you took the calf (for worship) after he (had gone) and you were unjust
  2,52,then We pardoned you even after that so that you should be grateful
  2,53,And when We gave Musa the book (prescribed laws) and the distinction (between right and wrong) so that you may receive guidance
  2,54,"and when Musa said to his people, \"O my people ! you have certainly been unjust to yourselves by taking the calf (for worship) so turn towards your Purifier then kill yourselves, this is better for you (than calf worship), in the sight of your Purifier,\" then He turned to you (mercifully), He is certainly the Accepter of repentance, the Merciful"
  2,55,"And when you said, \"O Musa ! We will never believe in you till we see Allah openly,\" so you were caught (by the) thunder-bolt while you were seeing"
  2,56,then We raised you after your death so that you should be grateful
  2,57,"And We provided shade over you (through) the clouds and sent down manna and quails over you, \"Eat of the good things which We have provided for you.\" And they did not harm Us but they were unjust to themselves"
  2,58,"And when We said, \"Enter this city and eat from it freely from wherever you like and enter the gate prostrating and say: Put down from us our heavy burdens, We will forgive you your mistakes and give more to the doers of good"
  2,59,"then those who were unjust, changed the word to other than what was said to them. So We sent down over those who were unjust punishment from the sky, because they were transgressors. (R)"